<plot>During July and August of 2007, indigenous filmmakers in Bolivia took their films across the country, hosting free screenings and staging debates and discussions about how best to reform the country. This film follows the events and discussions of this tour, providing a brief look into the roots of the indigenous filmmaking movement in Bolivia, the philosophy behind it, its relevance today, and its hopes and aims for the future.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?422801</url></doc>
